<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 18 at 4:54AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Slippery spots possible on untreated surfaces early this
morning...
Temperatures will continue to hover near freezing through the
next few hours for portions of the Capital District, Schoharie
Valley, Taconics, and Berkshires, and Mid Hudson Valley. Areas of
freezing rain and freezing drizzle are possible where the
temperature remains at or below freezing. This may lead to
slippery travel conditions on untreated roads and walkways. Patchy
black ice is also possible on untreated roadways and parking lots.
Motorists are advised to use caution.</description>
